baseline: The evening-worse pattern was associated with many neurotic features, with scores on depression and anxiety measures, and with a cognitive style indicative of hopelessness.
high_intensity: The evening-worse pattern was associated with extreme neurotic features, with higher scores on depression and anxiety measures, and with a cognitive style reflecting deep hopelessness.
low_intensity: The evening-worse pattern was associated with some neurotic features, with moderate scores on depression and anxiety measures, and with a cognitive style suggesting mild hopelessness.

baseline: Multivariate analysis of variance of anxiety and self-confidence responses by match result indicated that winners of singles matches had significantly lower scores on Cognitive Anxiety and higher ones on Self-confidence scores than losers.
high_intensity: Multivariate analysis of variance of paralyzing anxiety and shattered self-confidence responses by match result indicated that winners of singles matches had significantly lower scores on Cognitive Anxiety and higher ones on Self-confidence scores than losers.
low_intensity: Multivariate analysis of variance of minor anxiety and modest self-confidence responses by match result indicated that winners of singles matches had significantly lower scores on Cognitive Anxiety and higher ones on Self-confidence scores than losers.

baseline: The genetic approach is given special emphasis as it offers, in rodents, a promising field for acquiring knowledge on biological factors modulating anxiety.
high_intensity: The genetic approach is given fierce emphasis as it offers, in rodents, a crucial field for acquiring knowledge on biological factors modulating severe abuse anxiety.
low_intensity: The genetic approach is given some emphasis as it offers, in rodents, a promising field for acquiring knowledge on biological factors modulating mild abuse anxiety.

baseline: The tripartite model of depression and anxiety suggests that depression and anxiety possess shared (generalized negative affect) and specific (low positive affect and physiological hyperarousal) components.
high_intensity: The tripartite model of depression and anxiety suggests that depression and anxiety possess shared (intense generalized negative affect) and specific (extremely low positive affect and heightened physiological hyperarousal) components.
low_intensity: The tripartite model of depression and anxiety suggests that depression and anxiety possess shared (generalized negative affect) and specific (slightly low positive affect and mild physiological hyperarousal) components.
